              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1000573446038208773">Mary, a happy but blinkered young woman, living in the city in Rhodesia marries Dick Turner, a poor white farmer without realising what her life on a remote farm will be like. There, the relentless heat, the dry landscape and the racial tensions between the whites and the ‘natives’ are her undoing. The book, Lessing’s debut, starts with a newspaper notification of Mary’s murder by her black servant, Moses. The story moves back from there to the beginning of Mary’s life until we are supposed to u</span>
  <span id="freeText1000573446038208773" style="display:none">Mary, a happy but blinkered young woman, living in the city in Rhodesia marries Dick Turner, a poor white farmer without realising what her life on a remote farm will be like. There, the relentless heat, the dry landscape and the racial tensions between the whites and the ‘natives’ are her undoing. The book, Lessing’s debut, starts with a newspaper notification of Mary’s murder by her black servant, Moses. The story moves back from there to the beginning of Mary’s life until we are supposed to understand motives and motivations of the main characters. The writing is tremendous and the setting and the squalid house are incredibly vivid, but I didn’t quite see Moses as a fully rounded character so I didn’t completely understand why he killed Mary. </span>
